                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Mr. George Lamb, a jeweller in Cheapside. The prisoner came to the shop on the 6th of April, and asked for some diamond pins at 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I said we had none at that price, but I showed him four imitation diamond pins—two of them were 145. each, and two of them 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. each—he asked to look at another—I turned to get it, and he ran off with the four—I went to the door and called, "Police"—a policeman collared him two hundred yards off, and he dropped the pins.</p>
